<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="sites-layout-name-left-sidebar-hf sites-layout-vbox"><div class="sites-layout-tile sites-tile-name-header"><div dir="ltr"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);font-family:Trebuchet MS, arial, sans-serif;line-height:normal;white-space:pre"><span style="font-size:x-large"><b>Hugo Mercier's website</b></span></span></div></div><table cellspacing="0" class="sites-layout-hbox"><tbody><tr><td class="sites-layout-tile sites-tile-name-content-1 sites-canvas-sidebar"><div dir="ltr"><div dir="ltr"><p style="text-align:center;clear:both;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"><font face="'trebuchet ms'"><img height="200" src="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/_/rsrc/1256344691315/photo-medium.jpg?height=200&amp;width=178" style="border-top-width:0pt;border-right-width:0pt;border-bottom-width:0pt;border-left-width:0pt;border-top-style:none;border-right-style:none;border-bottom-style:none;border-left-style:none;border-color:initial" width="178" /></font></p><p style="text-align:left;margin-top:1em;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:1em;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;line-height:1.5"><span style="font-family:trebuchet ms;font-size:small">hmercier -at<span style="font-family:Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px"><span style="font-size:small"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">- sas.upenn.edu </font></span><b><font face="'trebuchet ms'"> </font></b></span></span></p><p style="text-align:left;font-size:1em;margin-top:1em;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:1em;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;line-height:1.5"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">(001) 215-746-3618 </font></p><div style="text-align:left"><a href="http://www.sas.upenn.edu/ppe/" rel="nofollow"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">PPE Program</font></a></div><div style="text-align:left"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">University of Pennsylvania</font></div><div style="text-align:left"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">313 Cohen Hall</font></div><div style="text-align:left"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">249 South 36th Street</font></div><div style="text-align:left"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">Philadelphia, PA 19104</font></div><p style="text-align:center;clear:both;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"><font face="'trebuchet ms'"><img src="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/_/rsrc/1256344692888/member-vignette-medium-init-.jpg" style="border-top-width:0px;border-right-width:0px;border-bottom-width:0px;border-left-width:0px;border-style:initial;border-color:initial" /><a href="http://www.cognitionandculture.net" rel="nofollow" style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)"><br />www.cognitionandculture.net</a></font></p></div><div dir="ltr"><p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:large"><br /></span></p></div></div></td><td class="sites-layout-tile sites-tile-name-content-2"><div dir="ltr"><blockquote style="margin:0 0 0 40px;border:none;padding:0px"><blockquote style="margin:0 0 0 40px;border:none;padding:0px"><span style="font-size:16px;line-height:24px"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">I'm a postdoc in the </font><a href="http://www.sas.upenn.edu/ppe/" rel="nofollow" style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">Philosophy, Politics and Economics</font></a><font face="'trebuchet ms'"> program at the University of Pennsylvania.</font></span>
<p><font size="4"><span style="font-size:16px;line-height:24px"><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/projects"><font color="#000000"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">Here is an overview of the projects I'm working on.</font></font></a></span></font></p>
<p><font size="4"><span style="font-size:16px;line-height:24px"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">Most of this work has focused on the function and workings of reasoning. According to </font><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/theargumentativetheoryofreasoning"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">the argumentative theory of reasoning</font></a><font face="'trebuchet ms'">, the function of reasoning is argumentative: to find and evaluate arguments so as to convince others and only be convinced when it is appropriate. Accordingly, reasoning works well as an argumentative device, but quite poorly otherwise.</font></span></font></p><p><font size="4"><span style="font-size:16px;line-height:24px"><font face="'trebuchet ms'">I'm currently trying to expand these ideas beyond reasoning and to show that other cognitive mechanisms that are typically thought of as being part of individual cognition have in fact a mainly social function. This interest has led to the organization of the webconference "<a href="http://www.cognitionandculture.net/Social-decisions-workshop/workshop-decision-making-for-a-social-world.html" rel="nofollow">Decision Making for a Social World</a>" to be hosted on the ICCI website, starting February 2011.</font></span></font></p></blockquote></blockquote>
<blockquote style="margin:0 0 0 40px;border:none;padding:0px">
<blockquote style="margin:0 0 0 40px;border:none;padding:0px"><span style="font-size:16px;line-height:24px"><font face="'trebuchet ms'"><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/publications">Here's a list of publications</a></font><font face="'trebuchet ms'">.<br /><br />Resources related to teaching can be found <a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/teaching">here</a>.</font></span></blockquote>
</blockquote></div></td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sites-layout-tile sites-tile-name-footer"><div dir="ltr"><font size="4"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:18px"><font size="4">           <a href="http://hugo.mercier.googlepages.com/CV_Hugo_Mercier.pdf" style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);text-decoration:underline">CV</a></font><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)">            </span></span><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)"> </span><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/projects" style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);text-decoration:underline">Projects</a><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)">       </span></font><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)">    </span><span style="font-size:18px;line-height:27px"><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/colleagues" style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);text-decoration:underline">Colleagues</a></span><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)">            </span><font size="4"><a href="http://www.cognitionandculture.net/" rel="nofollow" style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);text-decoration:underline">Blog</a><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)">       </span><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/hugomercier/teaching" style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);text-decoration:underline"><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51)">Teaching</span></a></font></div></div></div>
